content.problemStatement:
In this lesson, we'll learn how to use nested for loops in Java to print different patterns using characters or symbols. Pattern printing is a great way to practice loop control and understand nested loops effectively.

---

**Example: Printing a Right-Angled Triangle of Stars**
```java
class Seedit {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int rows = 5; // Number of rows in the pattern

        // Outer loop for each row
        for (int i = 1; i <= rows; i++) {
            // Inner loop to print stars in each row
            for (int j = 1; j <= i; j++) {
                System.out.print("*");
            }
            // Move to the next line after each row
            System.out.println();
        }
    }
}
```

**Expected Output:**
```default
*
**
***
****
*****
```

